3-30:The only way for a node to recommend a product is to first buy it .
3-31:Note that even if all nodes j buy a product, only the edge to the node jk that first made the purchase (within a week after the recommendation) will be marked by a buy bit .
3-32:Because the buy bit is set only for the first person who acts on a recommendation, we identify additional purchases by the presence of outgoing recommendations for a person, since all recommendations must be preceded by a purchase .
3-33:We call this type of evidence of purchase a buyedge .
3-34:Note that buy edges provide only a lower bound on the total number of purchases without discounts .
3-35:It is possible for a customer to not be the first to act on a recommendation and also to not recommend the product to others .
3-36:Unfortunately, this was not recorded in the data set .
3-37:We consider, however, the buy bits and buy edges as proxies for the total number of purchases through recommendations .
3-38:For each product group we took recommendations on all products from the group and created a network .
