3-96:Each cascade is a network consisting of customers (nodes) who purchased the same product as a result of each other"s recommendations (edges) .
3-97:We delete late recommendations all incoming recommendations that happened after the first purchase of the product .
3-98:This way we make the network time increasing or causal for each node all incoming edges (recommendations) occurred before all outgoing edges .
3-99:Now each connected component represents a time obeying propagation of recommendations .
