4 SUCCESS OF RECOMMENDATIONS :
4-1:So far we only looked into the aggregate statistics of the recommendation network .
4-2:Next, we ask questions about the effectiveness of recommendations in the recommendation network itself .
4-3:First, we analyze the probability of purchasing as one gets more and more recommendations .
4-4:Next, we measure recommendation effectiveness as two people exchange more and more recommendations .
4-5:Lastly, we observe the recommendation network from the perspective of the sender of the recommendation .
4-6:Does a node that makes more recommendations also influence more purchases? 3.1 Probability of buying versus number of incoming recommendations First, we examine how the probability of purchasing changes as one gets more and more recommendations .
4-7:One would expect that a person is more likely to buy a product if she gets more recommendations .
4-8:On the other had one would also think that there is a saturation point if a person hasn"t bought a product after a number of recommendations, they are not likely to change their minds after receiving even more of them .
4-9:So, how many recommendations are too many? Figure 5 shows the probability of purchasing a product as a function of the number of incoming recommendations on the product .
4-10:As we move to higher numbers of incoming recommendations, the number of observations drops rapidly .
4-11:For example, there were 5 million cases with 1 incoming recommendation on a book, and only 58 cases where a person got 20 incoming recommendations on a particular book .
4-12:The maximum was 30 incoming recommendations .
4-13:For these reasons we cut off the plot when the number of observations becomes too small and the error bars too large .
4-14:Figure 5(a) shows that, overall, book recommendations are rarely followed .
4-15:Even more surprisingly, as more and more recommendations are received, their success decreases .
4-16:We observe a peak in probability of buying at 2 incoming recommendations and then a slow drop .
4-17:For DVDs (figure 5(b)) we observe a saturation around 10 incoming recommendations .
4-18:This means that after a person gets 10 recommendations on a particular DVD, they become immune to them their probability of buying does not increase anymore .
4-19:The number of observations is 2.5 million at 1 incoming recommendation and 100 at 60 incoming recommendations .
